| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191027173042/https://www.nytimes.com/1947/08/30/archives/denham-is-reported-determined-to-keep-antired-affidavit-rule.html
| url-status = live
}}</ref> In October 1947, the NRLB overruled him, which meant that top officers of the [[American Federation of Labor]] (AFL) and [[Congress of Industrial Organizations]] (CIO) would not have to sign an anti-Communist oath per the Taft–Hartley Act.<ref>{{cite news
| title = National Affairs: Reversal
| publisher = TIME
| url = http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,804309,00.html
| date = 20 October 1947
| access-date = 28 October 2019
